LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = process by which liquids or other inanimate objects move from one place to another
= action by which humans, deities, or animals move forward, usually towards a specific destination
= action by which humans, deities, or animals move through an area without a specific destination
= causative action or process by which humans or deities cause (other) humans or objects to move forward, usually towards a specific destination
= process by which humans or deities follow a certain pattern of behavior, ◄ which is described as their journey through life
= causative process by which humans cause other humans to follow a certain pattern of behavior, ◄ which is described as their journey through life
literally: (one's) knees turn to water; hence: = to lose (one's) courage
literally: to go; hence: = process by which living creatures live their life until the moment of death
= process by which someone is going to die, described as a movement in one way only
= process by which an object vanishes from existence
= process by which events take place, ◄ as if they move like objects
literally: to go away; hence: = process by which an event stops happening
literally: to bring (one's) shame; = causative process by which humans deal with their shame

Glosses.Gloss: to bring (one's) shame > to hide (one's) disgrace

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to go to (one's) life; hence: = action by which humans move away from a certain place in order to save their life from danger
= process by which events continue over a prolonged period of time, ◄ described as movement along time
= person who spends much time on the road, either as well-intentioned traveller or as roaming vagabond
literally: to walk at (someone's) feet; hence: = action by which humans accompany other humans to serve them
= action by which humans approach (other) humans for having sexual relations

Glosses.Gloss: to go to > have sex with

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = state in which something exists in space, of which the existence is described as a movement from one place to another
